## Step 2: Annotation Guidelines

For consistent, high-quality labels across all annotators:

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Tight boxes** | Bounding boxes must closely fit the visible object — no excessive padding |
| **Occluded objects** | Annotate if >50% of the object is visible |
| **Class precision** | `helix` = cylindrical ribbon; `cluster` = dense spherical grouping |
| **Minimum size** | Ignore objects smaller than 10×10 pixels |
| **Overlap** | Allowed — each object gets its own box |

